ooostephen wrote:It hasn't warmed for 15+ years, but the globe is still warming? The salient point is that none of the models allowed for greater than a 10yr pause in temps, with a 95% certainty. Those models were clearly wrong, and all their predictions go out the window.Actually, if you account for variables that affect the atmospheric temperature and that the models were not intended to predict (El Nino/La Nina cycles, solar cycles, volcanic eruptions) then not only has the atmospheric warming continued unabated, the models are bang-on.In other words, any conclusion (for or against the AGW hypothesis or specific models) is invalid unless you determine what the temperature would have been without the effect of e.g. the prolonged solar minimum. As it turns out without that we would be even hotter. As predicted.
